Data Structures

Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
DACOMMS_tag_sStartMsg
diseqc_io_block_tThis structure defines the DiSEqC I/O operation block object. These objects are used internally by the driver
diseqc_port_settings_tThis structure contains initialisation parameters
diseqc_port_tThis structure defines the DiSEqC port object. The State member should be set to DISEQC_PORT_STATE_UNINITIALISED prior to a DISEQCInit call
diseqc_receive_timings_tThis structure defines the DiSEqC receive timings. Each bit received consists of 3 'chunks'. A 0 is defined as two active chunks followed by 1 inactive chunk. A 1 is defined as 1 active chunk followed by 2 inactive chunks
diseqc_send_timings_tThis structure defines the DiSEqC send timings. Each bit sent consists of 2 'chunks'. A 0 is defined as a long active chunk followed by a short inactive chunk. A 1 is defined as a short active chunk followed by a long inactive chunk

gpio_pin_tThis structure describes a GPIO pin logical object. It contains all context required by a single GPIO pin
